NTARI IXP Peering Policy
========================
Version: 1.0
Effective: {{DATE}}

1. GENERAL
   This exchange operates on an open peering policy for all connected members
   in good standing. Members must agree to these terms before activation.

2. TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS
   - Valid registered ASN (ARIN, RIPE, APNIC, or equivalent RIR)
   - Route announcements must match IRR records (bgpq4-verified)
   - No announcement of more-specific prefixes than /24 (IPv4) or /48 (IPv6)
   - No announcement of default route (0.0.0.0/0 or ::/0)
   - RPKI ROA records are strongly encouraged

3. ROUTE SERVER
   - Route server ASN: {{RS_ASN}}
   - Route server IP (IPv4): {{RS_IP4}}
   - Route server IP (IPv6): {{RS_IP6}}
   - Route server operates with rs-client semantics (no next-hop rewrite)

4. PREFIX LIMITS
   - Maximum {{MAX_PREFIXES}} prefixes per member session
   - Exceeding the limit results in session teardown and restart

5. ACCEPTABLE USE
   - No DDoS sourcing from peering LAN
   - No traffic manipulation (no community-based blackholing of other members)
   - Incident response: contact@ntari.org

6. GOVERNANCE
   Peering policy is governed by NTARI cooperative membership rules.
   See: https://ntari.org/governance
